All the `HomClass` business looks very reasonable, except for that one regression
Ah, that looks better! Must be some change in elaboration

Should this one also come with an adaptation note?
```suggestion
  #adaptation_note
  /--
  After https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/pull/5376 we need to search for this instance explicitly.
  -/
    infer_instance
```

More specifically, it's that `convert` isn't solving it by typeclass search anymore, but just spitting out an unsolved implicit argument.

If there's anything to do here, it is to change the behaviour of `convert` to more agressively solve such goals with `infer_instance` itself.

```suggestion
    #adaptation_note
    /--
    After https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/pull/5376 we need to search for this instance explicitly.
    TODO: change `convert` to more agressively solve such goals with `infer_instance` itself.
    -/
    infer_instance
```
